		<section name="Technologies">
			<p>The used technologies are:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Connected Limited Device Configuration (CLDC) 1.1</li>
				<li>Connected Device Configuration (CDC) 1.1.2</li>
				<li>Mobile Information Device Profile (MIDP) 2.0</li>
				<li>Java SE 6</li>
				<li>AAMM 1.1</li>
				<li>ActiveMQ 5.3.0</li>
				<li>ProGuard 4.4</li>
				<li>ASM 3.1</li>
				<li>Simple Logging Facade 1.6.0</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
		
		<section name="Requirements">
			<p>The requirements depend on which MicroJIAC edition you intend to use.</p>
			<subsection name="MIDlet-based">
				<p>For MIDlet-based MicroJIAC editions you need on the host system:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>32-bit CPU</li>
					<li>2 MB RAM</li>
					<li>CLDC &gt;=1.1 and MIDP &gt;=2.0 / IMP &gt;=1.0</li>
				</ul>
			</subsection>
			<subsection name="CDC-based">
				<p>For CDC-based MicroJIAC editions you need on the host system:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>32-bit CPU</li>
					<li>8 MB RAM</li>
					<li>CDC &gt;=1.1.2 and an appropriate Profile</li>
				</ul>
			</subsection>
			<subsection name="Java6-based">
				<p>For Java6-based MicroJIAC editions you need on the host system:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>500 MHz CPU</li>
					<li>256 MB RAM</li>
					<li>Java 6 or higher</li>
				</ul>
			</subsection>
			<p>The build environment always (= for all MicroJIAC editions) needs the following:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>1 GHz CPU</li>
				<li>512 MB RAM</li>
				<li>installed Java 6 or higher</li>
				<li>installed Maven 3 or higher</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
	</body>
